1
00:00:11,041 --> 00:00:12,250
[RACHEL]
I'm not giving you orders

2
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:14,208
or wanting favors.

3
00:00:14,291 --> 00:00:16,541
I'm just asking for your sake.

4
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:20,125
What about you?

5
00:00:25,416 --> 00:00:28,416
[bell rings, fades]

6
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:31,541
♪

7
00:00:39,041 --> 00:00:40,666
[sighs]

8
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:43,291
No matter what kinda
vacant expression you may have

9
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:44,625
on your face right now,

10
00:00:44,708 --> 00:00:47,875
it's still way too hard
to hold myself back.

11
00:00:47,958 --> 00:00:50,875
I mean, if I knew how to stop
myself from murderin' people,

12
00:00:50,958 --> 00:00:52,625
I wouldn't have been
brought to this building

13
00:00:52,708 --> 00:00:54,875
to begin with, now would I?

14
00:00:54,958 --> 00:00:57,958
♪

15
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:02,250
[grunts]

16
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:09,416
[inaudible]

17
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:15,333
[sighs]

18
00:01:18,208 --> 00:01:19,625
[shudders]

19
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,875
[groans]

20
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:30,708
♪

21
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:46,708
[WOMAN screaming]

22
00:01:50,416 --> 00:01:52,416
[ZACK]
Oh.

23
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:54,791
I get it.

24
00:01:54,875 --> 00:01:56,041
[music stops]

25
00:01:58,791 --> 00:02:00,958
Yeah, I know
how to fix my problem.

26
00:02:02,791 --> 00:02:05,791
♪

27
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:23,708
[groans]

28
00:02:23,791 --> 00:02:25,666
[shudders]

29
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:26,916
[ZACK grunting]

30
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:34,083
[panting]

31
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:35,833
[stabbing]

32
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:38,750
[exhales]

33
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,083
[laughing menacingly]

34
00:02:58,333 --> 00:03:02,041
Thing is, like I said before,
I can't stand a liar.

35
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:06,250
And you know what I mean
when I say that, don't ya?

36
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:07,250
Mm-hmm.

37
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:10,375
There's a good girl, Ray.

38
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:14,166
So, for now, do me one favor.

39
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:17,166
I'm beggin' ya.

40
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:19,458
Please don't let me
kill you just yet.

41
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:28,166
[groaning]

42
00:03:34,541 --> 00:03:35,583
[gasps]

43
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:38,833
[continues groaning]

44
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:44,791
[RACHEL]
It's not like before.

45
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:48,458
I'm not running to save myself.

46
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:50,583
This is to save Zack.

47
00:03:50,666 --> 00:03:51,666
[laughing]

48
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:53,791
[RACHEL]
For his sake,

49
00:03:53,875 --> 00:03:55,500
I can't let him kill me yet.

50
00:05:26,583 --> 00:05:27,875
[panting]

51
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:30,333
[ZACK laughing menacingly]

52
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:42,458
[RACHEL] Those drugs made him
lose his mind.

53
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:44,000
I have to keep running.

54
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:49,416
[ZACK laughing]

55
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:55,000
[gasps]

56
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,208
-It's a dead end.
-[door opens]

57
00:06:03,291 --> 00:06:04,666
[gasps]

58
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:06,875
[ZACK grunting]

59
00:06:12,875 --> 00:06:13,791
Zack, stop.

60
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,625
[ZACK laughing]

61
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:33,000
[gunshot]

62
00:06:33,083 --> 00:06:34,166
[gasps]

63
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:35,250
[ZACK gags]

64
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:42,166
[CATHY laughing]

65
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:43,333
Hi.

66
00:06:43,416 --> 00:06:45,583
I can't believe
you two made it this far.

67
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:48,208
Sorry I had to cut
the party short.

68
00:06:48,291 --> 00:06:50,625
And just when it was
getting good, too.

69
00:06:50,708 --> 00:06:52,541
You've entered
my firing squad room,

70
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,541
hence the bullet in your arm.

71
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:56,041
Look around you.

72
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:57,958
You're surrounded with
more machine guns

73
00:06:58,041 --> 00:06:59,291
than you can shake a scythe at.

74
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:01,375
And the best part is,
I'm able to control

75
00:07:01,458 --> 00:07:03,583
every one of them
with the push of a button.

76
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:05,333
It's just the handiest thing.

77
00:07:05,416 --> 00:07:07,583
Anyway, it sounds like
you've had a spat.

78
00:07:07,666 --> 00:07:09,833
It's fun watching
the drama unfold.

79
00:07:09,916 --> 00:07:11,875
Especially with you, Zack.

80
00:07:11,958 --> 00:07:15,000
You truly are exceeding
my expectations as a criminal.

81
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:17,208
The way you surrender
to your evil impulses,

82
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:20,000
despite your every
desperate effort to resist them.

83
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:22,208
It takes my breath away.

84
00:07:22,291 --> 00:07:24,458
[ZACK groaning]

85
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:26,208
Shut your damn mouth.

86
00:07:30,791 --> 00:07:34,333
[grunting]

87
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:35,541
What's the matter?

88
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:36,791
Feeling a little dopey?

89
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:39,291
Those drugs threw you
for a loop, didn't they?

90
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:41,458
You're attacking
the wrong person.

91
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:43,166
Doesn't make
no difference to me.

92
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,291
-[gunfire]
-[groans]

93
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:47,666
[CATHY]
You adorable oaf.

94
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:50,541
I already told you, dear,
you've got the wrong girl.

95
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:52,500
Oh, no.

96
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:53,875
Don't come near me!

97
00:07:53,958 --> 00:07:56,166
-[shuddering]
-[sighs]

98
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:00,000
That's interesting.

99
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:01,625
I was thinking
a gunshot wound or two

100
00:08:01,708 --> 00:08:03,541
would make you
more rational, but, nope.

101
00:08:03,625 --> 00:08:05,416
Same old Zack.

102
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,791
So sad.

103
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:10,500
[chuckles]
You can't help it.

104
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:12,125
Moving on.

105
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:13,583
Rachel Gardner.

106
00:08:13,666 --> 00:08:14,708
[snaps fingers]

107
00:08:14,791 --> 00:08:18,291
[drumroll]

108
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:23,833
[CATHY]
How about we even the odds?

109
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:26,916
It looks like poor Zack
brought a scythe to a gun fight.

110
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:27,958
Go on.

111
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:29,666
Slaughter each other.

112
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:31,875
And then,
whoever's left standing

113
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:34,708
will receive an even more
glorious judgment from me.

114
00:08:34,791 --> 00:08:37,000
-[laughing]
-[ZACK grunting]

115
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:39,958
But if we do that,

116
00:08:40,041 --> 00:08:41,666
then what'll be
the meaning of it?

117
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,375
Unh.

118
00:08:43,458 --> 00:08:44,958
Ugh.

119
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:46,583
You really are
a boring little sinner,

120
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:47,666
do you know that?

121
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:54,458
What's the point
in looking for meaning?

122
00:08:54,541 --> 00:08:57,208
Do you think that would change
what's happening?

123
00:08:57,291 --> 00:08:59,333
After all, nothing good
can ever come

124
00:08:59,416 --> 00:09:01,166
from the actions of a criminal,

125
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:02,750
so why try to understand?

126
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,125
You could find much better ways
to waste your time.

127
00:09:06,208 --> 00:09:08,208
Are you ready
for the main event?

128
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:11,333
I am, so put on a good show
for me, will you, darling?

129
00:09:11,416 --> 00:09:13,833
[applause over speakers]

130
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,333
[shudders]

131
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:24,208
[ZACK]
Come on!

132
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:26,625
If you're gonna shoot me,
then just do it already.

133
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:34,541
[CATHY]
What's this?

134
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:35,833
Do my eyes deceive me,

135
00:09:35,916 --> 00:09:38,375
or is somebody getting
a little gun-shy?

136
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:40,000
I should've expected as much

137
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:42,583
from an unremarkable girl
like you.

138
00:09:42,666 --> 00:09:43,500
Be quiet.

139
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:45,750
Even if you don't fire the gun,

140
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:48,000
I can't stop myself
from cuttin' you open.

141
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:56,500
I won't kill you.

142
00:09:56,583 --> 00:10:00,208
Oh, yeah? Well I wanna kill you
so bad it's tearin' me up!

143
00:10:00,291 --> 00:10:02,000
I'm sorry, Zack.

144
00:10:02,083 --> 00:10:03,166
I guess you'll have to do it

145
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,708
while I still have
this dull expression.

146
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:06,291
Damn right, I will!

147
00:10:06,375 --> 00:10:08,750
And I'll feel like shit
once I finish the job, too.

148
00:10:09,875 --> 00:10:12,083
I'm gonna give you
one more chance to stop me.

149
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:14,458
If you shoot me at point blank,
there's no way you can miss.

150
00:10:15,583 --> 00:10:16,666
Mm-mmm.

151
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:20,916
Ask all you want,
but my answer won't change.

152
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,500
I'm not going to kill you, Zack.

153
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:25,833
That's the decision I've made.

154
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:28,291
I'll be happy
for you to kill me.

155
00:10:28,375 --> 00:10:32,750
But I won't let this end
the way she wants.

156
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:36,125
Because, that woman,
she's wrong.

157
00:10:36,208 --> 00:10:38,375
We're not tools.

158
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:45,291
To murder, or give in to death,
they're our choices to make.

159
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:46,708
And ours alone.

160
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:54,333
[laughing]

161
00:10:54,416 --> 00:10:56,458
Jesus, you sure picked
a bad time

162
00:10:56,541 --> 00:10:58,125
to start givin' a damn.

163
00:10:58,208 --> 00:11:00,125
I can't hold back anymore.

164
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:01,375
Hey.

165
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,625
Try smilin' one more time.
Come on.

166
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,666
[grunting]

167
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:20,958
What a lame smile.

168
00:11:21,041 --> 00:11:24,208
Man, can't you have some life
in your eyes for five seconds?

169
00:11:24,291 --> 00:11:25,541
Oh, well.

170
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:28,041
If it did turn into
a real smile one day,

171
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:30,041
I'd love that!

172
00:11:30,125 --> 00:11:32,916
When I think about how fun
it would be to kill you then,

173
00:11:33,916 --> 00:11:36,291
it starts to make me smile too.

174
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:40,500
See, Ray,
look how glad I am now.

175
00:11:40,583 --> 00:11:43,875
So glad, it makes me
wanna kill myself!

176
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:51,000
[gasps]

177
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:52,500
♪

178
00:11:58,375 --> 00:12:00,083
[thuds]

179
00:12:03,125 --> 00:12:03,958
Zack, no.

180
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:06,541
[screaming]

181
00:12:07,875 --> 00:12:09,750
[gasps]

182
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:11,750
[CATHY]
It makes me so angry.

183
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:14,208
Neither one of you
is my ideal criminal.

184
00:12:14,291 --> 00:12:17,041
Rachel Gardner couldn't
deign herself to commit murder,

185
00:12:17,125 --> 00:12:19,166
and Isaac Foster turned out
to be such an imbecile

186
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,375
that he did himself in

187
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:22,458
just to satisfy
his own bloodlust.

188
00:12:22,541 --> 00:12:23,833
You're failures.

189
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:26,541
How dare you deny me
the pleasure of punishing you?

190
00:12:26,625 --> 00:12:29,000
You're such a supremely
dreary little brat, Rachel.

191
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:31,791
Sorry, but I already knew that

192
00:12:31,875 --> 00:12:33,416
without you
having to point it out.

193
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,375
[grunts]

194
00:12:35,916 --> 00:12:36,875
Talk back to me again

195
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:39,166
and see what happens,
young lady.

196
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:42,250
Do you think it's fun
judging someone so passive?

197
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:45,500
It hurts me much more
than it hurts you, Rachel.

198
00:12:45,583 --> 00:12:46,625
Honestly.

199
00:12:46,708 --> 00:12:48,750
I wish it would've been
Zack who lived.

200
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:50,000
He would have looked
so much better

201
00:12:50,083 --> 00:12:51,791
with his body all riddled
with bullet holes

202
00:12:51,875 --> 00:12:53,458
than you're about to.

203
00:12:54,916 --> 00:12:57,791
But, no, you couldn't even
pull the trigger.

204
00:12:57,875 --> 00:13:00,791
You're a disappointment
as a criminal.

205
00:13:00,875 --> 00:13:04,333
Ugh, how did you even
make it this far?

206
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:07,791
How? Let's see.

207
00:13:07,875 --> 00:13:09,375
[sighs]

208
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:10,791
I don't really care.

209
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:13,208
[whirring]

210
00:13:15,875 --> 00:13:17,375
-[ZACK gags]
-[gasps]

211
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:19,708
[panting]

212
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:20,958
Oh, my goodness.

213
00:13:21,041 --> 00:13:22,041
Still kicking, are we?

214
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:25,625
-Fabulous.
-[ZACK groaning]

215
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:28,000
[laughing]

216
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,375
You're going to kill him?

217
00:13:32,916 --> 00:13:34,291
Of course.

218
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:37,208
Such a fantastic criminal
deserves quality punishment.

219
00:13:37,291 --> 00:13:39,625
And I'm the only woman
suited for the job.

220
00:13:40,708 --> 00:13:41,666
[gun clicks]

221
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:42,750
[RACHEL]
You can't.

222
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:44,250
Well, now.

223
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,083
Look who's finally
showing some teeth.

224
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:49,583
Go ahead,
you've got a clear shot.

225
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:52,166
You just need the guts
to follow through.

226
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,541
You're no fun at all.

227
00:13:57,625 --> 00:13:59,750
And I almost thought
you might do it.

228
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:01,250
Not that it matters.

229
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,041
Even if you had been
brave enough to shoot,

230
00:14:03,125 --> 00:14:05,333
there were never any bullets
in that gun anyway.

231
00:14:05,416 --> 00:14:06,291
[gasps]

232
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:07,375
Too bad.

233
00:14:07,458 --> 00:14:08,541
You were close
to redeeming yourself

234
00:14:08,625 --> 00:14:10,000
as a criminal in my eyes,

235
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:11,916
but you've gone and found
another way to let me down,

236
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,291
haven't you, dear?

237
00:14:13,375 --> 00:14:14,875
That said,

238
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:16,666
I did appreciate
how spunky you were

239
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:19,458
when you pointed that gun at me.

240
00:14:19,541 --> 00:14:20,625
-Bang.
-[gunshot]

241
00:14:20,708 --> 00:14:21,625
[gasps]

242
00:14:23,625 --> 00:14:24,791
[groans]

243
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:30,166
-[groans]
-I'm glad you're not dead.

244
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:31,833
The more life a sinner has left,

245
00:14:31,916 --> 00:14:33,583
the more enjoyable
they are to punish.

246
00:14:33,666 --> 00:14:36,041
[laughing]

247
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:44,958
♪

248
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:50,416
[bell rings, fades]

249
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,875
[RACHEL]
No.

250
00:14:51,958 --> 00:14:53,375
You can't kill him now.

251
00:14:54,375 --> 00:14:57,250
Because Zack is the only one...

252
00:15:00,041 --> 00:15:01,208
who can kill me.

253
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:03,666
Bang, bang.

254
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:05,458
[CATHY gagging]

255
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,500
You!

256
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:15,208
Worthless tramp.

257
00:15:15,291 --> 00:15:17,041
You finally showed
your true colors.

258
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:19,000
Now you're a real criminal.

259
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:20,666
Oh, I love it.

260
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,375
Get ready to be punished.

261
00:15:22,458 --> 00:15:25,166
This is your day of reckoning,
you wretched sinner!

262
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:28,541
Make whatever disinterested face
you want, it doesn't matter.

263
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:30,708
I'll make sure you pay dearly!

264
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,333
Shut up, already.

265
00:15:37,666 --> 00:15:40,958
Nobody should ever look
that excited about bein' shot.

266
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:44,500
Seein' you like that made me
wanna cut you open so bad,

267
00:15:44,583 --> 00:15:46,791
it brought me
right outta my funk.

268
